review_blob: Really excellent tasting, looking and smelling weiss. Extremely smooth beer with a head that lasts until the very end of the glass. Very refreshing as well.
Undistinctive looking, it was pretty anonymous except for the *nuts* taste of hops. Pretty bitter after a swallow.
Really pale looking beer, has a thin head after pouring. Tastes nice and smooth without excessive carbonation. Little sweeter than I would have hoped, not bad though.

The first hefe-weizen I ever tasted, and it wasnt half bad. Lovely soft texture with a light smell. Nice, faint banana taste with wheat lingering after a smooth mouthful. Looks good, has a nice fluffy head.
This is probably one of the better beers on tap in Ireland, and its just not great. Theres a little bit of stale hoppy flavour from it, way to acidic for me.

The things nightmares are made of, I wouldnt drink this for free. What little taste there is consists of your grandmothers mothball-filled sock drawer. No taste, no aroma, I wish there was no flavour. Dreadful.

Another classic party beer - everything about it is just about all right if you get it from someone else. Virtually no taste, it does a quick and nasty job on your senses which can be useful when needed.
Pretty nice beer, it poured with a nice head. Pretty smooth after a slightly bitter smell, it was crisp and refreshing even after a few of them.
This is a pretty good beer - everything that Heineken, Bud America and Carlsberg with they were. Heavier than the usual crap on tap, this is really refreshing with a strong taste and lovely head.
Just another party beer - nothing special by a long shot. No head, bit too bubbly for me. At least its better than Bud.

My favourite stout in Cork - great stuff. Far lighter and creamier than Guinness, it loses some of the body but gains smoothness. Very light scent and comparitively short aftertaste. Another fine example of Irish beer xenophobia though, you have to try this one in Cork..

The reason people come to Ireland, this beer just doesnt travel overseas. Comparing the few Ive had in Canada, England and France to Irish Guinness is pointless, theyre just not the same - it has to be double pulled at least! Looks great, smells fantastic with a broadly roasted taste that combines perfectly with the creamy texture and the head. Has a mild, bitter aftertaste thats just about the perfect duration for a really enjoyable drink.
Goo hefeweizen - looks excellent with a huge head, tasted a little too sweet -more of a summer beer I think.
Wasnt great by a long way - it looked all right to start with, but I thought the taste was particularly bitter for a wheat beer.
Great looking beer that smells really fresh and crisp. Tasted the same, fresh bubblegum flavours all throughout with a nice whack of wheat to finish with on the aftertaste.
I paid a lot of cash for 6 bottles of these, and By God was I let down. Terrible, it makes Heineken look like the nectar of the gods.
Not bad, I felt a little queasy after a few pints of it though. Nice for the occasional sup.
Nice stout with a great roasted smell. Medium weight with a slightly bitter aftertaste. Sampled in Central.
Lovely golden colour, beautiful frothy white head. Very smooth beer that tastes mildly of banana with a strong wheaty aftertaste. Good from both Porterhouse Central and North.
